# 2.0.0 transport delta — Connect-RPC (proto codegen)

This directory is the **2.0.0 transport delta** for the `full-stack-monorepo`
flagship. It is an **additive** sibling of the frozen flat 1.0.0
`shared/protos/buf.gen.yaml.tmpl`, which is **byte-untouched** (B.8.2 maintenance
freeze; NFR-B86-002). It declares the modernized Connect-RPC codegen + Rust crate
line that B.8.12 (zero-regression) and B.8.14 (version bump) depend on.

It coexists with the flat 1.0.0 tree exactly as `2.0.0/infra/k8s/envoy-gateway/`
(B.8.4), `2.0.0/infra/postgres/` (B.8.5), and `2.0.0.yaml` (B.8.3) coexist with
their frozen 1.0.0 siblings. The `forge init` scaffolder still emits the flat
1.0.0 codegen manifest + grpc-api crate by default (the 2.0.0 candidate is
`scaffoldable: false`); this subtree is an additive on-disk asset spliced into
the 2.0.0 stack at B.8.10/B.8.14.

## Connect-RPC is the 2.0.0 default transport

Connect-RPC is the **default** edge / client transport for the 2.0.0 line
(`transport.yaml::protocol: connect-rpc`). A single handler exposes the
Connect+proto, Connect+JSON, gRPC, and gRPC-Web wire formats on the same routes.
Native gRPC (tonic) remains the inter-service transport (Article VII.2 gRPC SHALL
— the `neoeinstein-tonic` plugin is retained in `buf.gen.yaml`).

