## Policy source — `transport.yaml` (CONSUMED, not pinned inline)

The Connect-RPC protocol default + the 2.0.0-line crate pins are
**policy-sourced** from `.forge/standards/transport.yaml` v1.3.0
(`protocol: connect-rpc`; `codegen.versions_2_0_0:` block). They are NOT pinned
as inline scalars in `2.0.0.yaml` (only the concrete crate pins live in the
`Cargo.toml.tmpl`; the *policy* lives in the standard — FR-B86-015, ADR-B86-005).
B.8.6 bumps `transport.yaml` 1.2.0 → 1.3.0 additively (header fix +
`versions_2_0_0` block); the 1.0.0-line `codegen.versions` map is byte-unchanged.

## Connect-Dart plugin — official identity + provenance

The Dart Connect stubs are generated by `buf.build/connectrpc/dart:v1.0.0` — the
**official** ConnectRPC plugin (published by `connectrpc.com`), NOT the abandoned
`protoc-gen-connect-dart-community` (skadero, abandoned 2022-09). The plan §4.2
`protoc-gen-connect-dart-community` naming is definitively stale (the naming
drift was resolved by t5-connect-codegen / FR-T5-CC-003). pub.dev latest = 1.0.0
(verify-then-pin provenance: `https://pub.dev/api/packages/connectrpc`, accessed
2026-06-02; evidence.md P-08, re-confirmed P-13 — no advancement since the 1.0.0
frozen pin).

## gRPC-Web-via-Envoy Fallback (Connect-Dart Risk #1)

Connect-Dart (`buf.build/connectrpc/dart:v1.0.0`) is the **default** Dart
transport for the 2.0.0 line. The fallback below is **conditional** — it is NOT
the default path (FR-B86-042).

**Risk #1** (plan §13 caveat 2): if Connect-Dart proves too fragile at the
B.8.14 deployment validation, the Flutter client can fall back to **gRPC-Web via
the B.8.4 Envoy Gateway** *without changing the Rust server* — the same handler
already multiplexes gRPC-Web on its routes, and the Envoy Gateway data-plane
manifests under `../../infra/k8s/envoy-gateway/` already route to the
`<project-name>-backend` Service. The fallback is therefore a client-side codegen
swap (Connect-Dart → standard gRPC-Web Dart stubs) plus the existing Envoy route,
not a server rewrite.

This subtree does **NOT** modify any file under
`../../infra/k8s/envoy-gateway/` (B.8.4 territory — FR-B86-041); it only
cross-references it as the fallback ingress. The fallback decision and any Envoy
route change are owned by B.8.14, not B.8.6.

## Scope re-defer — Rust S2S Connect client (B.8.12)

No Rust server-to-server Connect client template ships here. Wiring a correct
S2S client (TLS, auth, deadline propagation, retry policy) is a B.8.12 concern
(E2E migration tests, the zero-regression convergence gate). It is explicitly
**re-deferred to B.8.12** (ADR-B86-004; chain: ADR-T5-003 → ADR-B86-004 →
B.8.12), not silently omitted (FR-B86-014).
